god's creative power is beyond human comprehension do you agree isaiah for thus saith the lord that created the heavens god himself that formed the earth and made it he hath established it he created it to be inhabited i am the lord and there is none else isaiah for as the heavens are higher than the earth so are my ways higher than your ways and my thoughts than your thoughts hebrews through faith we understand that the worlds were framed by the word of god so that things which are seen were not made of things which do appear hebrews but without faith it is impossible to please him for he that cometh to god must believe that he and that he is a rewarder of them that diligently seek him genesis in the beginning god created the heaven and the earth colossians for by him were all things created that are in heaven and that are in earth visible and invisible whether there be thrones or dominions or principalities or powers all things were created by him and for him amen john in the beginning was the word and word was with god and the word was god he was in the beginning with god all thingg came into being through him and apart from him not one thing came into being which has come into being hallelujah as believers we can have some realization of this wonderful creator by believing by faith into him we can lay hold of a small measure of our god and creator as we worship him in spirit and truthfulness our god's creative power is truly beyond our comprehension and not just his creative power but to this day science has yet to explore the vastness of this creation from the tiniest leaf to the galaxies of outer space to think that this amazing creator who stretch forth his hand and made the heavens and earth has made a spirit within man even our human spirit is ranked with the heavens and earth god also creates in us a new heart how precious is this oh how i love him how i adore him my breath my sunshine my all in all the great creator became my savior and all god's fulness 